snippet: A dozen trains, perhaps more, may have passed over the spot where the body of Emily Singleton, 22, lay in a deep trough at the end of the Canal Street station on Sunday.
abstract: New York City police identify woman's body found below the downtown platform of the No 1 train at Canal Street station as that of Emily Singleton, 22, of Brooklyn; police do not classify the death as a homicide but have no explanation for how she perished or why her body went unnoticed for nearly 12 hours.
lead_paragraph: A dozen trains, perhaps more, may have passed over the spot where the body of Emily Singleton, 22, lay in a deep trough at the end of the Canal Street station on Sunday.

headline.seo: Body on Subway Tracks Unnoticed for Hours
headline.main: Woman’s Corpse Lay Hidden for Hours on Tracks at Subway Station
